added.title: Dragon Run
added.description: Thomas has the honor of pulling the dragon to the Medieval Faire, but everyone wants a turn as well.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Biggest Adventure Club
added.description: When Thomas finds a treasure map he creates "The Big Adventure Club," to seek the treasure, but when Sandy wants to join, Thomas says she's too little, so Sandy forms her own club.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Big Whifflesnooze
added.description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

added.title: Lonesome Lucas
added.description: Lucas wakes up and it is still night. He tries to occupy himself until sun up. The house takes on a different persona at night. It scares Lucas a little and he feels alone because everyone else is still fast asleep. How long can one night alone last?

added.title: Caillou's Big Slide/Caillou Walks a Dog/Caillou Watches Rosie/Caillou Gets Sick/Caillou's Phone Call
added.description: Caillou is playing in the park with Clementine./Grandma is looking after her friend's dog again./Mommy isn't feeling well./Caillou has a fever./Mom is busy on the phone all morning.

added.title: Snails Forever
added.description: Chep wants to return a favor to Mush-Mush, but all Mush-Mush wants is to have a compost pancake on Pancake Day! But when the Food Snail falls for, and takes off after, the Travel Snail, Pancake Day has to be cancelled. Chep sees an opportunity to save the day for his friend! But er, how do you solve a snail falling for another?

added.title: The Creature from the Chocolate Chip
added.description: Sylvester eats all of Granny's cookies then makes up a cookie monster to blame.

added.title: Frog
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: A Present for Elly
added.description: Pocoyo decides to make a very special birthday present for Elly. Can you guess what it is?

added.title: Mixed Signals
added.description: The team receives a video message from Tenderheart that their mission has successfully ended and they can return home. Cheer suspects something about the message is wrong, but other members of the team don't agree. Cheer courageously stands her ground and keeps the team together while she solves the mystery, and reveals the message was faked by Bluster.

added.title: I Can't See You
added.description: Being a chameleon, Bodhi is brilliant at hide and seek. But when he celebrates victory in Lucas' face, Lucas decides to beat him once and for all. Using flour to follow Bodhi's prints, Lucas wins easily. When he realizes that he's upset Bodhi by beating him at his special thing, he's really sorry and Bodhi is sorry too for celebrating so ungraciously.

added.title: Goes Camping/Learns to Skate/Gets Dressed/Daddy/Grows Carrots
added.description: Caillou hears about Daddy's first camping trip./Caillou has a hard time skating./Mom's doing the laundry./Mom and Rosie are out for the day. Caillou and Dad will spend the day together./Grandpa helps Mom make a vegetable garden.

added.title: Fool the Forest
added.description: It's Fool The Forest Day when Mushables pull pranks, and MM has an epic one planned. But they spill Chanterelle's painting dye and instead must replace it by finding a rare Sloof beetle and milking it for its dye in front of everyone. Wait a minute! You can't milk a beetle! They've been pranked!

added.title: Parking Lot
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: Pocoyo Dance
added.description: Pocoyo finds a radio. Pato does his funny, funky dance and Elly demonstrates her delicate ballet style. Pocoyo hears a tune he likes and finds his groove. Everyone can dance in their own special way!

added.title: Card Bored Box
added.description: Faced with nothing to do, the babies use a cardboard box and their imaginations to make playtime fun.

added.title: Thomas' Day Off
added.description: When all the trains but Thomas get deliveries, he's left to spend the day alone. With the help of an old boxcar and a battered beachball... an adventure unfolds.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Star Helpers
added.description: Starmush's back is stuck, and the Mushelder has no choice but to ask for help in Mushton. Because Chep is the one that finds a solution to his back problem, Starmush chooses him to help with his daily activities. But Mush-Mush is jealous, he would have loved being the chosen one…

added.title: Puff's Perfect Picnic
added.description: Because he has won the moss-ball game last year, Puff is in charge of organizing this Summer's Picnic. Only Puff isn't comfortable in that role. Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit offer to help and make sure all the Mushables will follow Puff's lead. Gradually, Puff gains confidence and ends up bossing everyone around. Now, all the Mushables are about to flee the Picnic!

added.title: Bubbles
added.description: Bing and Pando are learning how to make bubbles, but will Bing be able to blow his own bubble?

added.title: Pato's Egg
added.description: Pato finds an egg and immediately falls in love with it: he wants to take care of the little baby inside the egg. When the egg hatches he gets the shock of his life: it's not a cute little duckling at all, but a very odd looking spider. His friends are terrified of the little creature and won't play with Pato if he brings it along. Pato rather craftily and meanly makes the little spider go away and do things on its own, so Pato can play with Pocoyo and Elly. Finally the little spider makes their hearts melt when he shows them that there's nothing to be scared of and he just wants to be their friend.

added.title: Caillou the Road Builder/Caillou's Building Adventure/A House in the Sky
added.description: There's been a big storm and the playschool yard is littered with branches./When Daddy and Grandpa help a charity build a new home for a needy family, Caillou comes along./Mommy and Caillou go to visit an old friend of Mom's.

added.title: Lights! Camera! Tweety!
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes are very eager to visit the local TV station, home of their favorite live children's show. When Floyd accidentally locks them inside the studio moments before airtime, they are forced to put on today's program all by themselves!

added.title: Backstage Bugs
added.description: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

removed.title: Things That Go Bugs in the Night
removed.description: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

removed.title: Ducks
removed.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

removed.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
removed.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

removed.title: Boo
removed.description: Lucas discovers that it's best to ask your friends permission before you give them a scare on Halloween. He adopts the guise of a ghost and the use of decorative masks and sneaky hiding places to give them all the jumps.

removed.title: Mushlers to the Rescue
removed.description: Having rescued a Mushlet, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit become heroes in Mushton, and they're loving it! So Mushlers create a rescue team but alas, no one needs saving! How can you be a hero when there is nothing to be heroic about? Then when some Mushlets become adrift on the river, Team Mush-Mush, with Morel's help, have to save the day again.

removed.title: Never Boop a Robot
removed.description: When Lucas sees a robot on the shelf he boops it. This sets off the clockwork mechanism and now Lucas is pursued around the house by a B Movie robot. When Bodhi gets cornered, Lucas realizes he's got to help his friend.

removed.title: Race the Beast
removed.description: Mush-Mush and his friends are determined to win the bark sledge race, but their essential fourth team member drops out. Our friends ask Mushpot to step up from being their coach to racing with them. The Mushelder is reluctant at first but soon reveals the tough competitor he is!

removed.title: A Little Cloud
removed.description: Pocoyo has an unusual new friend: a lonely little cloud who just wants to play.

removed.title: Plays Baby/Flies on a Plane/In the Bathtub/Goes Birdwatching/The Doll
removed.description: Caillou thinks his sister Rosie is getting favorable treatment./It's Caillou's first flight./It's bathtime, and for Caillou that means trouble./Grandma always has the best surprises./Mom is putting on her makeup to go out with Dad.

removed.title: Kana Goes Slow
removed.description: When Kana's power goes out during a delivery run, Thomas teaches her that sometimes it's okay to go slow.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Smoothie
removed.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

removed.title: Fetch Loula Fetch!
removed.description: Pocoyo and Loula are going to the beach, but they keep losing their ball. They learn about colors, shapes and sizes as they meet their friends along the way.

removed.title: A Quiet Delivery
removed.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
removed.description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

removed.title: Looks for Gilbert/Surprise Breakfast/Missing Sock/Goes to Work/Quarrel
removed.description: Caillou is having a game of dinosaur hunter with Gilbert the cat./Caillou gets up early one morning./Caillou wants to wear his favorite socks, but one of them is missing./Caillou goes to work with Mom./Clementine comes over to play.

removed.title: School Daze
removed.description: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing.
